# Implementation Plan — Trip Budget Tracker v2 Upgrade

This document outlines the design and implementation steps for upgrading the client-side Trip Budget Tracker with new features: multi-currency support with live FX rates, receipt photo attachments, UPI/PayPal deep-link settlement, expense category visualization, and PDF summary export.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **UPI & PayPal VPAs/Usernames:** For deep-links to succeed, payees must have UPI IDs (VPAs) and PayPal usernames. We plan to update the `AddMemberForm` to include optional fields for these so that the settlement engine can build correct links.
> 
> **Package Installations:** We need to install `jspdf` to generate the PDF report, and `canvas-confetti` (optional) or use standard HTML/SVG for the pie chart. We will request your approval to run `npm install jspdf` during execution.

## Open Questions

> [!WARNING]
> 1. **Redux Persistence:** Since the app resets on reload, should we implement simple `localStorage` synchronization for the Redux store to avoid losing active trips and receipt photo attachments?
> 2. **Live FX API Key:** To prevent key exposure as per PRD security guidelines, we will use a keyless public currency API (`https://open.er-api.com/v6/latest/`) directly from the browser. Is this approach approved?

